        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 28 at 1:25PM MDT until September 28 at 2:00PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 120 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Acala, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Hancock, Acala, and McNary. Portions of I-10 between mile
markers 63 and 78.

The strongest portion of this storm remains just southwest of the
International Border, near San Jose de Paredes and Guadalupe
Victoria. It has started to turn more towards the east and is
slowing down. The worst part of the storm will most likely affect
areas just south of Acala and west of Fort Hancock very soon.
</description>
        <instruction>Prepare immediately for large hail and damaging winds. People outside
should move to a shelter, inside a strong building and away from
windows.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
